Charge density
$$
\begin{aligned}
&\rho=\frac{\text { charge }}{\text { volume }}=\frac{q}{A d} \Rightarrow q=\rho A d \\
&\text { Also, } q=I T \Rightarrow T=\frac{q}{I}=\frac{\rho A d}{I}
\end{aligned}
$$

According to Gauss's Law
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \int(\text { E.dA })=\mathrm{q}_0 / \varepsilon_0 \Rightarrow \mathrm{q}=\varepsilon_0\left(\phi_2-\phi_1\right) \\
& {\left[\text { since } \phi=\int \mathrm{E} \cdot \mathrm{dA}\right]}
\end{aligned}
$$
